                            <comment id="15152096" author="stephanewen" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 10:24:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just be make sure I get this correctly:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Regular sources do not emit a MAX_LONG watermark at the end&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sources that we know will never have data emit one immediately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Is that what you have in mind?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15152164" author="aljoscha" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 11:15:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that&apos;s what I had in mind.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The second part is only necessary because we cannot shutdown sources because that would break watermarks/checkpoints. If we could correctly close them and that information would be taken into account by the checkpoint barrier logic and the watermark logic we wouldn&apos;t need it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15152263" author="stephanewen" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 12:47:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, the checkpoint barrier logic handles closed sources.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15152264" author="stephanewen" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 12:48:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, to some extend. Checkpoints do not block on closed sources, but will not succeed either.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15152428" author="aljoscha" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 15:16:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that&apos;s what I meant. If a source closes no more checkpoints will be performed. The input processor just has to listen for channel closed events, though, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15152769" author="jgrier" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 18:22:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aljoscha&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aljoscha&quot;&gt;aljoscha&lt;/a&gt; Just a quick question on this.  In the description you said: &quot;At one point we decided to not emit in-flight windows when closing the topology or sources.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is still the case, correct?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15153996" author="aljoscha" created="Fri, 19 Feb 2016 09:44:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jgrier&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jgrier&quot;&gt;jgrier&lt;/a&gt; Yes, this is still the case. It just seems that we did not go all the way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
